How They Grow



How Diamonds Grow








1




Inspect diamond seeds carefully to ensure they are free of inclusions.








2


Take a Peek


Prepare the surface for growth and place diamond seeds on growth platform.








3







Control chamber pressure and temperature.





4






Inject ultra-pure carbon-rich gases and other gases into the chamber.








5






Excite the gases to an energy level where they form a plasma.





6





Let it rain. High-energy carbon precipitates out of a plasma cloud and is deposited on the seeds. The atoms are of sufficient energy that they form the diamond allotrope, rather than the lower energy graphite allotrope.








7




See In Action


Let it grow. Wafer seeds gradually become diamond crystals, building up at a consistent rate until they reach the desired thickness.








8





Open chamber and remove diamond crystals.





9




Slice and shape, using high-energy lasers, for industrial applications.
 See Diamonds for Industry




9








Cut and polish into gems for jewelry.
 See Diamonds for Jewelry














