Home»Investors»Investor resources»FAQs











1. Where is Scio Diamond’s corporate headquarters?
2. Who is Scio Diamond’s independent auditor?
3. When did Scio Diamond go public?
4. When is Scio Diamond’s fiscal year ended?
5. How are Scio Diamond’s shares traded? 
6. Does Scio Diamond pay dividends?
7. Who is Scio Diamond’s stock transfer agent?
8. How do I transfer stock, change the address on my shareholder account, or replace a lost stock certificate?
10. How can I purchase Scio Diamond shares?
11. How can I remove a “Restricted Legend” from my Scio Diamond stock certificate?
12. How can I sell shares that have a “Restricted Legend”?
13. When is Scio’s next earnings release?
14. Whom should I contact regarding investor inquiries? 
15. Where can I find all of the SEC filings for Scio? Where can I download and view quarterly and annual reports?
16. What is Scio Diamond’s CUSIP? 
17. How do I get added to the Scio Diamond email distribution list? 
18. How can I get a copy of the annual report?



1. Where is Scio Diamond’s corporate headquarters?
Scio Diamond Technology Corp headquarters is located at the NEXT Innovation Center in Greenville, South Carolina.  Our address is:
411 University Ridge, Suite 110
Greenville, SC 29601
back to top

2. Who is Scio Diamond’s independent auditor?
Scio Diamond uses Cherry Bekaert, LLP, a nationally recognized growth oriented CPA firm.
back to top

3. When did Scio Diamond go public?
Scio’s Diamond’s shares began publicly trading in September, 2011.
back to top

4. When is Scio Diamond’s fiscal year ended?
Scio’s fiscal year runs from April 1 to March 31.
back to top

5. How are Scio Diamond’s shares traded? 
Scio Diamond Technology Corporation (Scio) stock is traded on the OTC Bulletin Board and the OTC PINK marketplace under the symbol SCIO.
back to top

6. Does Scio Diamond pay dividends?
Scio has not paid dividends and does not have current plans to pay dividends in the future.
back to top

7. Who is Scio Diamond’s stock transfer agent?
Scio uses Empire Stock Transfer of Henderson, NV as our transfer agent.
back to top

8. How do I transfer stock, change the address on my shareholder account, or replace a lost stock certificate?
Please contact our transfer agent:
EMPIRE STOCK TRANSFER INC.
1859 Whitney Mesa Dr.
Henderson, NV 89014
Phone: (702) 818-5898
Fax: (702) 974-1444
Email: info@empirestock.com
back to top

10. How can I purchase Scio Diamond shares?
Scio Diamond Technology Corporation (Scio) stock is traded on the OTC Bulletin Board and the OTC PINK marketplace under the symbol SCIO.
back to top

11. How can I remove a “Restricted Legend” from my Scio Diamond stock certificate?
Shareholders of Scio Diamond have restricted legends on their shares because they participated in a direct stock offering of the company. These shares have not been registered with the SEC. The restricted legend can only be removed by selling the stock. SEC regulations do not permit the company to remove the legend without a corresponding stock sale.
back to top

12. How can I sell shares that have a “Restricted Legend”?
Shareholders with shares that have “Restricted Legends” and meet certain criteria can be sold through your stock broker. Your stock broker should contact our transfer agent, Empire Stock Transfer or contact the company at investorrelations@sciodiamond.com.
back to top

13. When is Scio’s next earnings release?
Scio has a fiscal year that begins April 1 and ends March 31. Our fiscal quarters end on June 30, September 30, December 31 and March 31. Our quarterly results will be published within 45 days of the fiscal quarter end, and our year end results will be published within 90 days of fiscal year end and in accordance with filling guidelines.
back to top

14. Whom should I contact regarding investor inquiries? 
Please send emails to investorrelations@sciodiamond.com.
back to top

15. Where can I find all of the SEC filings for Scio? Where can I download and view quarterly and annual reports?
All of Scio Diamond’s SEC Filings can be found in the EDGAR archives at SEC.gov or on the investor relations page of our website.
back to top

16. What is Scio Diamond’s CUSIP? 
Our CUSIP is 808831101
back to top

17. How do I get added to the Scio Diamond email distribution list? 
Please sign up on our investor relations page.
back to top

18. How can I get a copy of the annual report?
Our annual report can be found on the investor relations page of our website.
back to top








